The paper focuses on fraud detection in online social networks, specifically Facebook, which falls under the category of social networking (cs.SOC). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms (cs.IR) and graph-based fraud detection algorithms (cs.CR) to detect like farms. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of lexical and interaction-based features (cs.SI) to detect like farm accounts. Finally, the paper discusses the need to counter reputation manipulation activities (cs.CYBER).
